The paper proposes a new algorithm for multi-view clustering that can handle incomplete views. This problem is common in machine learning and data analysis, and the proposed algorithm is based on weighted semi-nonnegative matrix factorization. The paper also discusses the use of $L_{2,1}$-Norm regularized regression to reduce the influence of missing instances. Given these topics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
